review_blob: One of my all-time favorites.  Dark mahogany color.  A strong beer with the perfect blend of sweet malt and hops.  Flavor is very deliciously unique putting this beer in a category all its own.
Hops, hops, hops.  Good copper color.  Nice citrusy aroma and flavor.  Perfect hop bitterness and dryness.  One awesome beer.

Stong roasty coffee flavor with a slight alcohol taste.  Slight hop flavor.  Not as thick in body as some Imperials.  Very good beer overall.  One of the reasons North Coast is one of my favorite breweries.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Nose is smoky.  Dark in color with a thick rich head.  Great flavor, very malty with a hint of chocolate.  One of the best doppelbocks out there.

I wish there were zeros in the ratings sections.  This isnt beer....its garbage, pure undeniable filth.  This was a college student special (Nattie Ice) where I went to school and I routinely talked smack to all of my friends that would buy this cheap trash.

Nice citrusy/floral aroma.  Lighter color than I expected with a nice creamy head.  Strong hop flavor (what else from 100+ IBUs).  Slight malty mouthfeel.  Nice dry finish.  The Stone crew takes pride in their IPAs and this is definitely is one to be proud of.

Just tried this one Saturday at Stones Anniversary tasting and it was awesome.  Roasty coffee aroma.  Tasty blend of coffee and chocolate flavors.  Slight tast of alcohol, but not overpowering by any means (especially at 12%).  Nice thick texture and a fresh dry finish.

This beer is one of my all-time favorites from the crew at Stone.  Perfect blend of roasty coffee and choclate flavor.  Dark black in color and a thick syrupy body.  Alcohol taste blends in perfectly with the great taste and is not overpowering, as it can be in other Imperial Stouts.
